title.narrative: By 2022, key stakeholders have capacity to develop, implement and monitor family/community based care for prevention and rehabilitation of children in contact with the law, children without family care and those who are victims of violence or exploitation

description.narrative: With UNICEF support, 15 states increased their knowledge on standards of care and capacities to provide protection and care to children without parental care. Capacities of 48,998 institutional functionaries were built on ensuring standards of care for children in institutions, benefiting 250,908 girls and boys. 6 states developed a road map for alternative care, focused on strengthening child care services, enhancement of standards of care, prevention of family separation, provision of psychosocial support to children in institutions. A study on youth leaving care completed in four states, enabled understanding on gaps in services and informed action plans. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2020
